QUESTION #44
Sandwiches: Write a function that accepts a array of items a person wants on a sandwich.
The function should have one parameter that collects as many items as the function call provides, 
and it should print a summary of the sandwich that is being ordered. Call the function three times, 
using a different number of arguments each time.
ANSWER
function sandwich(array_items){
  console.log( "I'll make you a great sandwich:");
  console.log("_________________________________");
  for (var i=0;i<array_items.length;i++){
    console.log(array_items[i]+" add in sandwich ")
  }
  console.log("sandwitch is ready");
}    
sandwich(["chicken","Cheese","tomato"]);
sandwich(["beef","pootato","chedderchesse"]);
sandwich(["vagetables","tomatoketchup","butter"]);
